#: ../../M/Murphys-Law.rst:5
msgid "Murphy's Law"
msgstr "Murphy's Law"

#: ../../M/Murphys-Law.rst:7
msgid "prov\\."
msgstr "ことわざ"

#: ../../M/Murphys-Law.rst:9
msgid ""
"The correct, *original* Murphy's Law reads: \"If there are two or more ways "
"to do something, and one of those ways can result in a catastrophe, then "
"someone will do it.\" This is a principle of defensive design, cited here "
"because it is usually given in mutant forms less descriptive of the "
"challenges of design for :ref:`luser`\\s. For example, you don't make a two-"
"pin plug symmetrical and then label it \"THIS WAY UP\"; if it matters which "
"way it is plugged in, then you make the design asymmetrical (see also the "
"anecdote under :ref:`magic-smoke`\\)."
msgstr ""
"正しい\\ *元の*\\ Murphy's "
"Lawはこう読む。「何かをするやり方が二つ以上あり、そのうちの一つが大惨事を招きうるなら、誰かがそれをやる」。これは防御的設計の原理であり、\\ "
":ref:`luser`\\ "
"のための設計の難しさをあまり描写しない変異した形で通常与えられるため、ここに引用する。たとえば、二ピンのプラグを対称にして「THIS WAY "
"UP(この面を上に)」と表示してはならない。差し込む向きが重要なら、設計を非対称にするのである(\\ :ref:`magic-smoke`\\ "
"の下の逸話も参照)。"

#: ../../M/Murphys-Law.rst:13
msgid ""
"Edward A. Murphy, Jr. was one of McDonnell-Douglas's test engineers on the "
"rocket-sled experiments that were done by the U.S. Air Force in 1949 to test"
" human acceleration tolerances (USAF project MX981). One experiment involved"
" a set of 16 accelerometers mounted to different parts of the subject's "
"body. There were two ways each sensor could be glued to its mount, and "
"somebody methodically installed all 16 in a replacement set the wrong way "
"around. Murphy then made the original form of his pronouncement, which the "
"test subject (Major John Paul Stapp) mis-quoted (apparently in the more "
"general form \"Whatever can go wrong, will go wrong)\" at a news conference "
"a few days later."
msgstr ""
"Edward A. Murphy, "
"Jr.は、1949年に米空軍が人間の加速度耐性をテストするために行ったロケットそりの実験(USAFプロジェクトMX981)におけるMcDonnell-"
"Douglasのテスト技術者の一人だった。ある実験では、被験者の体のさまざまな部分に取り付けられた16個の加速度計のセットが使われた。各センサーは台座に二通りの方法で接着でき、誰かが交換用のセットの16個すべてを几帳面に間違った向きに取り付けた。そこでMurphyは彼の宣言の元の形を述べ、被験者(Major"
" John Paul Stapp)が数日後の記者会見でそれをより一般的な形「間違いうるものは何であれ、間違うだろう」として(どうやら)誤って引用した。"

#: ../../M/Murphys-Law.rst:18
msgid ""
"Within months ‘Murphy's Law’ had spread to various technical cultures "
"connected to aerospace engineering. Before too many years had gone by "
"variants had passed into the popular imagination, changing as they went. "
"Most of these are variants on \"Anything that can go wrong, will\"; this is "
"more correctly referred to as :ref:`Finagles-Law`\\. The memetic drift "
"apparent in these mutants clearly demonstrates Murphy's Law acting on "
"itself!"
msgstr ""
"数か月のうちに‘Murphy's "
"Law’は航空宇宙工学につながるさまざまな技術文化に広まった。あまり年月が経たないうちに、変種は変化しながら大衆の想像に入り込んだ。これらのほとんどは「間違いうることは何であれ、間違うだろう」の変種である。これはより正しくは\\"
" :ref:`Finagles-Law`\\ と呼ばれる。これらの変異に表れるミーム的漂流は、Murphy's "
"Lawがそれ自身に作用していることを明確に示している!"
